setFontFamilyName

public void setFontFamilyName(java.lang.String name)
This method sets the font family name from the group code 1000. This method will also check to see if setPrimaryFontFileName(java.lang.String) succeeded and if it did then keep the font name it found and if it failed then substitute the font family name.

setPrimaryFontFileName

public void setPrimaryFontFileName(java.lang.String FFN)
Sets the primary font file name (group code 3 of style table). This method also attempts to set the logical font file name based on the true font name as listed within the actual font file itself. It does that by attempting to find the argument file and reading that file with Font.createFont(int, java.io.InputStream) method. and then calling the Font.getFontName() method that returns the logical font file name. For example:

If the argument font file is 'switzb.ttf' this method will attempt to find the file using either the default font directory or the directory passed as a URL from DxfPreprocessor. If the font can't be found on the system (this could happen if this is not the computer that the original drawings were created on), then the font family name is substituted from group code 1000. This could be an unsatisfactory situation because 'switzb.ttf' is actually Switzerland Bold but group code 1000 reports that this font is just Switzerland. The bold is a switch in the Style dialog box in AutoCAD and will not get set in the DXF output and therefore does not migrate to the Svg file.

Also note that a font directory can be entered on the command line with correct system slash orientation. This method is also responsible for converting the any '\' into a '/' as per true URL standard.

Parameters:
FFN - Font File Name.
